.SH NAME
ShadowRoot.pointerLockElement \- ShadowRoot: pointerLockElement property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]pointerLockElement\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]ShadowRoot\f[R] interface provides the element set as the target
for mouse events while the pointer is locked.
It is \f[CR]null\f[R] if lock is pending, pointer is unlocked, or the
target is in another tree.
.SH VALUE
An \f[CR]Element\f[R] or \f[CR]null\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] customElem = document.querySelector(\[dq]my\-shadow\-dom\-element\[dq]);
\f[B]let\f[R] shadow = customElem.shadowRoot;
\f[B]let\f[R] pleElem = shadow.pointerLockElement;
.EE
